55:55.185 --> 55:57.854
Oh. Miller time.

55:57.938 --> 56:00.023
Jesse, I've told you, like, 1 8 times

56:00.107 --> 56:01.399
that that's not what it means.

56:01.483 --> 56:04.193
Then what does it mean?

56:04.278 --> 56:06.946
I thought it was the right thing to do.

56:10.451 --> 56:12.285
What is your problem with him?

56:12.369 --> 56:13.786
(DOOR CLOSES)

56:13.871 --> 56:17.665
That guy put the snakes in our house.

56:19.001 --> 56:20.293
Why would he do that?

56:20.377 --> 56:22.545
Because he still thinks this is his house.

56:22.629 --> 56:23.713
He wants us out.

56:23.797 --> 56:25.548
Oh, come on.

56:25.632 --> 56:26.758
I'm sorry, Cooper.

56:26.842 --> 56:28.634
But I'm having trouble relating to this.

56:28.719 --> 56:31.888
Well, you don't seem to have
a hard time relating to him.

56:31.972 --> 56:33.765
Meaning what, exactly?

56:35.893 --> 56:38.936
You know exactly what I'm talking about.

56:47.321 --> 56:50.573
Dave Miller asked me to sleep with him.

56:53.368 --> 56:54.911
What?

57:01.460 --> 57:03.419
Dave Miller.

57:03.504 --> 57:06.631
Yeah. Dave Miller...

57:06.715 --> 57:09.550
Hit on me on the airplane.

57:09.635 --> 57:11.511
He offered me the V.P. spot

57:11.595 --> 57:15.098
and then asked me to spend
the night with him in Chicago.

57:17.684 --> 57:18.726
What did you do?

57:18.811 --> 57:19.852
What did I do?

57:19.937 --> 57:22.230
I moved out here into the middle
of nowhere with you.

57:22.314 --> 57:26.776
I turned into some...
Some 1 9th-century housewife,

57:26.860 --> 57:28.820
which was great for a while.

57:28.904 --> 57:31.072
It felt like this weight
was lifted off my shoulders.

57:31.156 --> 57:32.990
And you were the one who was
supposed to carry us through.

57:33.075 --> 57:34.784
But that is not what's happening.

57:34.868 --> 57:36.661
-We're... We're drowning here.
-No. No.

57:36.745 --> 57:38.704
-And it is time to get out.
-No. That's not what I said.

57:38.831 --> 57:41.165
I said, what did you do?

57:46.672 --> 57:48.965
I said yes.

57:53.137 --> 57:55.555
But then I called you on the phone.

57:56.890 --> 57:57.974
And that was the day

57:58.058 --> 58:01.811
that Jesse was very nearly
killed by that car.

58:01.895 --> 58:04.897
Cooper, that was a wake-up call for me.

58:06.108 --> 58:08.067
So, uh...

58:09.862 --> 58:10.820
(EXHALES DEEPLY)

58:10.904 --> 58:14.782
That's why you agreed to
come out here, right?

58:15.492 --> 58:17.076
(EXHALES DEEPLY)

58:28.797 --> 58:30.923
(BELL CHIMES)

58:31.008 --> 58:33.593
(ROCK MUSIC PLAYING IN DISTANCE)

58:41.768 --> 58:42.935
(BILLIARD BALLS CLACKING)

58:44.188 --> 58:45.396
Hey, buddy.

58:45.480 --> 58:46.772
-Hey.
-Hey. How are you?

58:46.857 --> 58:48.274
How's it going?

58:48.358 --> 58:50.359
Hey, I understand, uh,
Steph and Kristen,

58:50.444 --> 58:52.820
they're gonna go
on a shopping spree with their moms.

58:52.905 --> 58:54.030
-Yeah, yeah, yeah.
-(CHUCKLES)

58:54.114 --> 58:55.406
Hey, look. Can I buy you a drink?

58:55.490 --> 58:56.824
Uh, no. I got to get back.

58:56.909 --> 58:58.326
Oh, come on.
One beer's not gonna kill you.

58:58.410 --> 58:59.410
No.

58:59.494 --> 59:01.787
Look, Cooper.

59:01.872 --> 59:05.333
Word to the wise.
Be cool around here, okay?

59:05.417 --> 59:07.210
I didn't come here to start a war, Ray.

59:07.294 --> 59:08.294
Exactly.

59:08.378 --> 59:11.964
All I'm saying is come in,
buy a round of drinks,

59:12.049 --> 59:14.425
show there's no hard feelings
between you and Dale.

59:14.509 --> 59:15.801
What do you say?

59:17.304 --> 59:19.847
Come on. I'll buy you a beer.

59:19.932 --> 59:21.307
Come on.

59:23.477 --> 59:25.728
Drinks on Mr. Tilson.

59:25.812 --> 59:28.648
Thanks, Mr. Tilson. Appreciate it.

59:32.319 --> 59:34.487
RUBY: Dale...

59:34.571 --> 59:35.780
Dale...

59:35.864 --> 59:38.616
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

59:43.163 --> 59:44.872
-MAN: Yo, Mr. Tilson.
-(ROCK SONG PLAYING)

59:46.375 --> 59:48.542
Take the shot, man. Take the shot.

59:48.627 --> 59:51.003
Give me a kiss.

59:51.088 --> 59:55.258
<i>Well, I'm so tired
of crying but I'm out on the road again</i>

59:55.342 --> 59:57.593
<i>I'm on the road again</i>

59:57.678 --> 59:58.970
I want to play the game.

59:59.054 --> 01:00:00.471
<i>I ain't got no woman</i>

01:00:00.555 --> 01:00:03.266
<i>Just to call
my special friend</i>

01:00:05.644 --> 01:00:08.604
<i>You know the first time
l traveled out</i>

01:00:08.689 --> 01:00:10.439
<i>ln the rain and snow</i>

01:00:10.524 --> 01:00:13.109
<i>ln the rain and snow</i>

01:00:13.193 --> 01:00:16.028
<i>You know the first time
